              "legacy:stora-skramso"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A large but unfortunately difficult-to-access crag in the Stockholm archipelago.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:stora-skramso"
            ]
          }
        },
        "beskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Description",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:stora-skramso"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Stora Skramsö is located between Yxlö and Muskö in the southern Stockholm archipelago. The southern part of this elongated island is geologically very interesting with its steep southern cliff and three very deep cracks that divide the headland into massive slabs. If the crag were not so inaccessible, it would be one of the more popular climbing spots in the Stockholm area. Many of the routes are cluttered with numerous old rusty bolts that cannot be trusted. Place your own gear!",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:stora-skramso"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:stora-skramso"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "You can reach Stora Skramsö by boat, or if you are a good swimmer - drive to Yxlö and swim via Lilla Skramsö.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:stora-skramso"
            ]
          }
        },
